You can check your overall progress, including completion percentage, in statistics section inside of your pattern. Open side toolbar on the right and click on statistics icon.

content:
Great app. Usability is easy and effective. The only bad thing is that 
sometimes it won't start after several hours of being unused and you need 
to reboot your phone. (I'm using xiomi) However if you back up your work in 
Dropbox Everytime when you finish - crashing is not a problem.

I really love this app, the convenience, thought that went into creating it. But the fact that it crashes or simply doesn't open on my Android phone is getting really annoying. Just recently updated both the app and the phone and it doesn't open AGAIN. Dark screen and nothing happens. Renewed. Even uninstalled and installed again. Still all I see is a dark screen when it opens.

This is a really excellent app - very clean design, and extremely functional. I love that I can track my progress as I stitch (instead of using a highlighter on a piece of paper). It's really fantastic for cross-country stitchers - you can highlight a particular symbol/color and see where you have to stitch that particular symbol over the entire pattern. No more of those annoyances where you feel like you've found every symbol only to realize that you've missed two somewhere. It's got tools to help those who use parking as well.  My only gripe is that their website could do a better job of explaining each of the functions and how to use them best. But it's fairly intuitive to learn (took me about half an hour of exploring the program).   If you're using more recent versions of PCStitch (i.e., higher than 10), then you should export the pattern to a format that's compatible for this app (this is very easy to do in the PCStitch program).
